      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey im stuck at heathrow cuz my flight to singapore just got canceled... everything is a mess here. can u help me figure out what i should look for in new flights? i need to get there as fast as possible so what should i prioritize when looking at options?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can sense the frustration, but don't worry, I'm here to help you navigate this chaotic situation. When searching for new flights, it's essential to prioritize your needs, and in this case, getting to Singapore as quickly as possible is your top priority. You can think of it like a treasure hunt, where you're searching for the shortest route to your treasure – in this case, your Singaporean destination.\n\nWhen comparing flights, focus on the departure and arrival times, as well as the layovers. You want to find the flight with the shortest overall travel time, like a swift and agile little elf, dodging obstacles and reaching its destination quickly. Also, consider the airline's reputation, as some might be more reliable than others, like a sturdy old oak tree providing shelter from the storm.\n\nAnother crucial factor is the layovers, or \"gaps\" in your journey. You want to minimize these, just like a skilled thief trying to slip in and out of a crowded market unnoticed. Look for flights with shorter layovers or those that offer more direct routes. And, of course, don't forget to check the baggage policies, as you wouldn't want any unexpected \"goblin\" fees popping up at the last minute.",
