    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, what do you mean by \"'goblin' fees\"? i've never heard that term before. are there specific hidden costs or surcharges i should be looking out for with the airlines?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"goblin\" fees I mentioned are just a playful way to describe those sneaky, hidden costs that can pop up when you're booking flights. You see, airlines often have a few tricks up their sleeves, like a mischievous imp trying to snatch your hard-earned coins.\n\nOne common \"goblin\" fee is the baggage charge, which can add up quickly, especially if you're traveling with a lot of luggage. Some airlines might also charge extra for seat selection, meal options, or even printing your boarding pass. It's like a goblin trying to distract you with shiny objects while you're trying to keep track of your expenses.\n\nAnother sneaky \"goblin\" fee is the change or cancellation penalty. If you need to make changes to your flight, you might be charged a fee, which can be as steep as a mountain pass guarded by a fierce troll. So, it's essential to read the fine print and understand the airline's policies before booking your flight.\n\nTo avoid these \"goblin\" fees, be sure to carefully review the airline's website, and don't be afraid to ask questions if you're unsure about anything. And, of course, always keep an eye out for any hidden costs, just",
